snippet.title: Beetle Ju | Beetle Bug - PC Gameplay
snippet.description:
The first in the Beetle Bug series, this game saw a physical release in the September 2003 issue of CyberMycha Extra magazine in Poland, as well as a jewel case release in Germany and a keep case release in Spain. This game, as well as the rest of the series, are digitally available to download and play on iWin.com.

In Beetle Ju you control a little bug who has to overcome a variety of dangers. Help Beetle Ju through a labyrinth by digging up the path and moving or blowing up boulders. Different Weapons like grenades, rockets and bombs are available. Use these weapons against monsters and defeat a set number of them in every of the 100 levels.

Beetle Bug / Beetle Ju (C) gamigo AG
Developed by OXXO Media

#beelteju #beetlebug #oxxomedia #intenum #pc #cybermycha #cybermychaextra #cybermycha_extra #windows #casualgames

FUN FACT: The very same issue of CyberMycha Extra also included two shareware games (Snowball Run, Atomic Cannon), three trailers (Worms 3D, RC Cars, F1 Challenge 99-02), two wallpapers (Worms 3D, Chicken Shoot) and playable demos of Tony Hawk's Pro Skater 4, Jurassic Park: Operation Genesis and Next Generation Tennis 2003.
